OL,3,CAll-women shortlist announced for
OL,4,Cdebut crime writer prize
OL,6,FA prize for debut crime writers has an
OL,7,Fall-women shortlist for the first
OL,8,Ftime, organisers have announced.
OL,10,FFive authors are in the running for
OL,11,Fthe Bloody Scotland Debut Prize 2026,
OL,12,Fwith the winner set to be announced
OL,13,Fduring the Bloody Scotland festival in
OL,14,FStirling in September.
OL,16,FThe shortlist includes A Bad, Bad
OL,17,FPlace by Frances Crawford, who
OL,18,Fgraduated from the University of
OL,19,FGlasgow creative writing course aged
OL,20,F60, having been tutored by bestselling
OL,21,Fcrime writer Louise Welsh.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G1/7
