OL,3,CAll-women shortlist announced for
OL,4,Cdebut crime writer prize
OL,6,FAlso shortlisted are Original Sins by
OL,7,FLinda Duncan McLaughlin, a playwright
OL,8,Fand screenwriter for BBC Scotland's
OL,9,FRiver City, and We Know What You Did
OL,10,Fby Scottish journalist Kirsty Lockwood.
OL,12,FThe Vanishing Place by Zoe Rankin, who
OL,13,Fgrew up in Scotland but now lives in
OL,14,FNew Zealand, is also in the running,
OL,15,Fas is Liar Thief by May Rinaldi, who
OL,16,Flives in Dumfries and Galloway.
OL,18,FCrime writer Denise Mina, who is guest
OL,19,Fprogrammer for the festival,
OL,20,Fcongratulated the shortlisted authors.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/7
